<P>
Wambaugh concedes that maybe we are too free as a nation, that we may have to 
curtail our freedoms to a certain extent. At present, the Second Amendment 
right to keep and bear arms is abused to the point that this area is a 
battlefield. We need to leave the military assault weapons to the military and 
exercise the Second Amendment rights in a reasonable manner. 
</P>
