<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICE WITH A SCOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The good news is that Lee Green's article, "Service With a Scowl" (March 5), 
made me laugh more than once as I read of his encounters with various rude 
retailers. The bad news is he's right. A polite consumer doesn't stand a chance 
against abrasive retailers. Thus, one is forced to resort to similar behavior 
to survive. And so, the vicious circle continues; rude retailers create rude 
consumers, and on and on. Prof. Jerald Jellison could have helped by offering 
some suggestions on how to effectively diffuse such hostile confrontation 
between consumers and retailers. Then, maybe, we would have a "kinder, gentler" 
marketplace. 
</P>
<P>
MARY JO SHELTON-DUTCHER 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
