<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BRIEFS: HIGH-RENT DISTRICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID M. KINCHEN, From Staff Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Westside of Los Angeles, as well as the cities of Beverly Hills and West 
Hollywood, have some of the highest rents in the metropolitan area, according 
to a study by Grubb &amp; Ellis Co., a national real estate firm. 
</P>
<P>
A typical two-bedroom apartment in Westwood rents for $1,500 a month, requiring 
an annual salary of about $60,000, according to John F. Carpenter of the firm's 
West Los Angeles office. He said the study was done primarily for developers 
interested in building apartments and investors seeking to buy them. 
</P>
<P>
Typical two-bedroom apartments in Brentwood and Beverly Hills rent for $1,450 a 
month. The same size unit rents for $1,250 in West Hollywood and $1,150 in 
Hollywood, according to the study. 
</P>
</TEXT>
