<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stephen M. Chiles has been appointed senior vice president and manager of the 
real estate finance division of John Burnham &amp; Co. Chiles will supervise 
mortgage banking operations in the company's San Diego and Orange counties 
offices. 
</P>
<P>
Bart Tabor has been named first vice president and southwest area manager of 
Coldwell Banker Real Estate Finance Services, a national company which handles 
construction, permanent loans, plus joint venture and equity financing. Tabor 
will direct Coldwell's operations in Los Angeles, Newport Beach, La Jolla and 
Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
The mortgage banking firm of Dwyer-Curlett &amp; Co. has promoted Dolores C. 
Arriaga to assistant vice president of its loan closing division. The Los 
Angeles-based firm specializes in the placement of real estate financing with 
life insurance companies, pension funds and other institutional sources. 
</P>
<P>
Terry M. Hargrave has joined Janss Corp. of Los Angeles as chief financial 
officer. Her responsibilities for the commercial real estate development firm 
will include project financing, financial reporting and lender relations. 
</P>
<P>
Heller Real Estate Financial Services has named Kathryn B. Plouff assistant 
vice president and loan officer of its western region. Based in Beverly Hills, 
Plouff will work with mortgage brokers to provide interim programs based on 
cash flows to owners, investors and developers of commercial properties. 
</P>
<P>
Engineers 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Milton Meckler, chief executive officer and president of the Meckler 
Group in Encino, has been named a Fellow of the American Society of Mechanical 
Engineers. The society is a technical and educational organization which, among 
other commitments, sets many industrial and manufacturing standards. 
</P>
<P>
Developers 
</P>
<P>
Glen H. Sexton has been named president of Warmington Homes' North Counties 
Division (Los Angeles and Ventura). The 63-year-old, family-owned home-building 
firm is based in Costa Mesa. Sexton will work out of the company's Thousand 
Oaks office, directing the division's day-to-day operations. 
</P>
<P>
James A. Sinsheimer has been promoted to first vice president within the 
planning and construction department of Tishman West Co. The full-service real 
estate developer is headquartered in Los Angeles. Sinsheimer joined the firm in 
1984. 
</P>
<P>
Doerken Development Corp. of Lancaster has named Edward John Golden executive 
vice president. Headquartered in Santa Monica, Doerken will acquire and develop 
commercial and industrial projects in Antelope Valley and Kern County. 
</P>
<P>
Robert T. Pace has been appointed vice president and general counsel for the 
Hahn Co. Based in San Diego, the firm specializes in shopping centers. Pace 
will handle all of its transactions, litigation and corporate matters. 
</P>
<P>
Brokers 
</P>
<P>
Bryant Cos. of South Pasadena is one of the first real estate firms to join the 
newly formed Prudential Real Estate Affiliates Inc. Prudential expanded its 
services to incorporate real estate in 1988. David W. Bryant, founder and 
president of the Bryant Cos., has provided service to clients in residential 
and commercial sales, and property management since 1964. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine-based Scher-Volt Commercial Brokerage Co. has announced that Robert J. 
Socci has joined its Anaheim/Orange office as associate vice president. Socci 
will continue his specialty in industrial properties marketing and in leased 
investments. 
</P>
<P>
Architects 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Fourteen winners were announced in the 10th annual Interiors 
Magazine Design Competition; two were from Southern California: The Shimazu 
Partnership Architects of Marina del Rey, and William Adams Architect of Santa 
Monica. LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
