<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUNNING HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Gordon, you're a good man. How nice you are to fight to save the Dunning 
house when the owner could care less about its future. I give you a lot of 
credit to put so much dedication into a structure that you don't even own. 
</P>
<P>
I live in West Los Angeles, near Santa Monica, and it's so distressing to see 
them tear down quaint bungalows to put in these god-awful modern apartment 
buildings. 
</P>
<P>
All anyone cares about now is money. They don't think about the originality or 
history of a building. 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN MIGLIACCIO 
</P>
<P>
West Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
