<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUNNING HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My wife and I are in San Diego for the fifth consecutive spring, and read Paul 
Gordon's story about the Dunning house ("Fighting for the Survival of an Old 
House," April 9). If there was ever anything printed in your newspaper with 
human interest, that one should win the prize. 
</P>
<P>
Even out in my country (Montana), somewhat similar conditions have and still 
continue to be developing. And I would think this type of "happening" occurs 
most everywhere throughout our country. Things are continuously lost to 
developers' onslaughts. 
</P>
<P>
I am an architect and continuously look for new jobs, but not at the expense of 
losing our historical ties with the past -- especially the unique and 
irreplaceable past. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that Paul Gordon's message will stir similar feelings in your area. 
</P>
<P>
MAX KUHR 
</P>
<P>
Havre, Mont. 
</P>
</TEXT>
