<HEADLINE>
<P>
CINEFILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEONARD KLADY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Priscilla Presley plays "Girl Friday" to detective Andrew Dice Clay in Fox's 
"Ford Fairlane," filming locally next month. Look for romantic sparks along 
with dictation in the off-beat murder mystery from director Renny Harlin and 
producer Joel Silver. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Julia Roberts is an L.A. street prostitute set up in a plush suite by a 
visiting business acquisitor in Touchstone's "3000," which films in June. 
Steven Reuther and Arnon Milchan produce the dark "Pygmalion-ish" tale written 
by John Lawton and Stephen Metcalfe. Gary Marshall directs. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Matthew Modine and Daphne Zuniga have signed up for med school next month in 
Disney's "Gross Anatomy," a comedy in the "Paper Chase" mode. Thom Eberhardt 
directs the screenplay by Mark Spragge and Ron Nyswaner. Howard Rosenman and 
Debra Hill produce. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Raul Julia is Dr. Frankenstein in "Frankenstein Unbound," which marks the 
directorial return (a record 18-year hiatus) of Roger Corman. In Corman, Brian 
Aldis and F.X. Feeney's script, a 21st-Century scientist goes back two 
centuries to discover the literary creation was real. The Thom Mount Co. 
production gets underway in Bergamo, Italy in June. . . . In addition to 
writing-directing "My Father's Eyes," Lou Diamond Phillips now stars in the 
production next September. Phillips plays a young man -- seen in flashbacks -- 
who dies in a freak accident shortly after the birth of his son, who's now a 
teen-ager. Karen Allen co-stars in the Daniel Eisenberg production. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Rip Torn plays Walt Whitman in Cinepix's "Beautiful Dreamers," a romantic idyll 
filming next month in Toronto. Written and directed by John Kent Harris, the 
story centers on the writer's affair with a woman doctor in Canada during the 
1880s. Colm Feore and Wendel Meldrun co-star in the Steven Roth production. . . 
. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Ford's novel "Bright Angel" goes to screen this summer with Dermot 
Mulroney portraying a young man attempting to reconcile with his father. Sam 
Shepard plays the enigmatic dad in Ford's adaptation for director Michael 
Fields. Sue Baden-Powell, Page Simpson and Rob MacLean produce for Hemdale. . . 
. 
</P>
<P>
Guy Madison, TV's Wild Bill Hickock, and Rory Calhoun play old cowhands in 
Wouk/Ware's "Bad Jim." The shaggy dog western centers on a good guy who goes 
wrong after finding Billy the Kid's horse. John Clark Gable stars for 
writer-director Clyde Ware with filming set outside Phoenix next month. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Duet's Alison La Placa joins Orion's "Madhouse" as Kirstie Alley's very jealous 
older sister. Also added to the cast are John Diehl, Bradley Gregg and Robert 
Ginty, a befuddled neighbor who sees John Larroquette's peaceful home life 
crumble as friends and cousins invade. Leslie Dixon produces and Tom Ropelewski 
writes and directs next month in Tucson. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Donald Pleasence returns as Dr. Loomis in Galaxy's "Halloween 5: The Revenge of 
Michael Myers," a May start in Salt Lake City. In the new edition actress 
Danielle Harris has empathic responses with the demonic Michael Myers, who's in 
pursuit of Wendy Kaplan. Dominique Othenin-Gerard directs and co-wrote with 
Shem Bitterman and Michael Jacobs for producer Moustapha Akkad. . . . LEONARD 
KLADY 
</P>
</TEXT>
