<HEADLINE>
<P>
CENSUS BUREAU RECRUITS WORKERS FOR NEXT YEAR'S NATIONAL SURVEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Census takers for 1990 are being recruited in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
More than 600 temporary jobs are available from the U.S. Census Bureau. Workers 
will be employed for six weeks at $6 an hour. Paid training and car mileage are 
included. 
</P>
<P>
Qualified applicants must be U.S. citizens, 18 or older and take a written 
test. 
</P>
<P>
Census takers canvass designated areas by driving and walking -- usually close 
to their homes -- to check a prepared list of addresses with existing 
residential units. 
</P>
<P>
"Although the 1990 census will be taken about a year from now . . . we must 
prepare our mailing lists now to ensure that each household will receive its 
questionnaire in the mail," said John Reeder, Los Angeles regional director of 
the Census Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
Interested county residents should contact the Compton or Long Beach census 
offices. 
</P>
<P>
The Compton office is in the Compton Transit Center, 305 N. Tamarind St., Suite 
1A, Compton 90220. Telephone 762-1230 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
The Long Beach office is at 6621 E. Pacific Coast Highway, Suite 100, Long 
Beach 90803. For information phone 799-1329. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042389-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 47724 </DOCID>
