<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 26-year-old taxi driver was shot and killed in North Belfast, Northern 
Ireland, in a drive-by attack claimed by the outlawed Irish Republican Army. 
The driver, William Thompson of Belfast, was overtaken by another taxi and a 
masked man inside fired at him, police said. The IRA said in a statement that 
it had information that Thompson had been involved in sectarian murders. 
</P>
