<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former Zimbabwe government minister who ingested poison last week after being 
implicated in a corruption scandal died and will be buried at a shrine for 
revolutionary heroes today, officials said. Maurice Nyagumbo, 64, resigned as 
senior minister for political affairs last weekend after a presidential inquiry 
implicated him in black-market car deals. Nyagumbo died at Harare's main 
hospital Thursday night. Despite the scandal, officials said that Zimbabwe 
President Robert Mugabe declared Nyagumbo a national hero. 
</P>
</TEXT>
