SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNCIL ELECTS GRALOW MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ruth Gralow has been elected mayor of Palos Verdes Estates by her City Council 
colleagues, succeeding James Kinney. Councilman James R. Nyman will serve as 
mayor pro tem. 
</P>
<P>
Gralow has been on the Palos Verdes Estates council since 1984 and has been 
mayor once before. Nyman has been a member of the council for one year. 
</P>
<P>
In an address to the audience following her election, Gralow said she looks 
forward to hosting the city's 50th birthday celebration in December and to the 
reconstruction of the problem intersection where Palos Verdes Drives West and 
North meet. 
