<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOSPICE CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for your editorial supporting the conclusions of the Orange County 
Grand Jury report that recommends the establishment of hospice care in Orange 
County. The need is immediate and will increase substantially over the next 
decade. It now costs $150 per day per patient in a hospice facility, as opposed 
to $1,200 per day in an intensive care hospital unit. 
</P>
<P>
Our Hospice Orange County steering committee is building an organization to 
fund and operate a facility that will provide quality, compassionate care for 
terminally ill patients and give comfort and financial relief to their 
families. We are now evaluating business plan proposals from Coopers &amp; 
Lybrand, Ernst &amp; Whinney and a San Diego-based health care consulting firm. 
United Way has provided an office for us, and we have obtained a California 
Community Foundation Grant. 
</P>
<P>
Our broad-based committee has benefited from the generous participation of 
advisers, such as Corrine Bayley, vice president, St. Joseph Health System; Dr. 
Rex Ehling, county health officer; Penny Weismuller, AIDS coordinator of the 
county Health Care Agency, and many others knowledgeable in this field. 
</P>
<P>
We appreciate the efforts of the grand jury and its human services committee 
for bringing the critical issue of hospice care to the attention of the Board 
of Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
DR. ROSS CONNER 
</P>
<P>
SINDEE SMOLOWITZ 
</P>
<P>
Co-Chairs 
</P>
<P>
Hospice Orange County 
</P>
<P>
Steering Committee 
</P>
</TEXT>
