<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER VIETNAMESE AND FORMER CIA CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "Ex-CIA Chief Defends Role of Vietnamese in Little Saigon" (April 
17): I could not care less about how William Colby feels about the Vietnamese, 
and if I hear one more time that "the Vietnamese community in Orange County is 
known worldwide as the capital of the Vietnamese overseas," I will just scream! 
</P>
<P>
Why Orange County? With 49 other states to choose from, why settle in Orange 
County, in the Westminster, Garden Grove area? And then proceed to build 
garish, urban blight-type buildings here? How would the Vietnamese like it if 
an invader took over their country? How do they think we feel about them taking 
over our neighborhoods? 
</P>
<P>
For 15 years we have had to put up with more and more people moving into an 
area already heavily impacted. Just what have the Vietnamese immigrants 
contributed to this county and country other than more traffic, kids, crime and 
traffic congestion? I couldn't care less about how hard they work. We work hard 
or even harder than they do. And what do we get? An environment that is choking 
us by the presence of more Vietnamese. 
</P>
<P>
JENNIFER T. MOORE 
</P>
<P>
Westminster 
</P>
